36#define CHECK(op) \
37 do { result = (op); \
38 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) goto cleanup; \
39 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
40
41/*%
42 * Set up a logging category according to the named.conf data
43 * in 'ccat' and add it to 'logconfig'.
44 */
45static isc_result_t
46category_fromconf(const cfg_obj_t *ccat, isc_logconfig_t *logconfig) {
47 isc_result_t result;
48 const char *catname;
49 isc_logcategory_t *category;
50 isc_logmodule_t *module;
51 const cfg_obj_t *destinations = NULL;
52 const cfg_listelt_t *element = NULL;
53
54 catname = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_tuple_get(ccat, "name"));
55 category = isc_log_categorybyname(named_g_lctx, catname);
56 if (category == NULL) {
57 cfg_obj_log(ccat, named_g_lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
58 "unknown logging category '%s' ignored",
59 catname);
60 /*
61 * Allow further processing by returning success.
62 */
63 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
64 }
65
66 if (logconfig == NULL)
67 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
68
69 module = NULL;
70
71 destinations = cfg_tuple_get(ccat, "destinations");
72 for (element = cfg_list_first(destinations);
73 element != NULL;
74 element = cfg_list_next(element))
75 {
76 const cfg_obj_t *channel = cfg_listelt_value(element);
77 const char *channelname = cfg_obj_asstring(channel);
78
79 result = isc_log_usechannel(logconfig, channelname, category,
80 module);
81 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
82 isc_log_write(named_g_lctx, CFG_LOGCATEGORY_CONFIG,
83 NAMED_LOGMODULE_SERVER, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
84 "logging channel '%s': %s", channelname,
85 isc_result_totext(result));
86 return (result);
87 }
88 }
89 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
90}
91
92/*%
93 * Set up a logging channel according to the named.conf data
94 * in 'cchan' and add it to 'logconfig'.
95 */
96static isc_result_t
97channel_fromconf(const cfg_obj_t *channel, isc_logconfig_t *logconfig) {
98 isc_result_t result;
99 isc_logdestination_t dest;
100 unsigned int type;
101 unsigned int flags = 0;
102 int level;
103 const char *channelname;
104 const cfg_obj_t *fileobj = NULL;
105 const cfg_obj_t *syslogobj = NULL;
106 const cfg_obj_t *nullobj = NULL;
107 const cfg_obj_t *stderrobj = NULL;
108 const cfg_obj_t *severity = NULL;
109 int i;
110
111 channelname = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_map_getname(channel));
112
113 (void)cfg_map_get(channel, "file", &fileobj);
114 (void)cfg_map_get(channel, "syslog", &syslogobj);
115 (void)cfg_map_get(channel, "null", &nullobj);
116 (void)cfg_map_get(channel, "stderr", &stderrobj);
117
118 i = 0;
119 if (fileobj != NULL)
120 i++;
121 if (syslogobj != NULL)
122 i++;
123 if (nullobj != NULL)
124 i++;
125 if (stderrobj != NULL)
126 i++;
127
128 if (i != 1) {
129 cfg_obj_log(channel, named_g_lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
130 "channel '%s': exactly one of file, syslog, "
131 "null, and stderr must be present", channelname);
132 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
133 }
134
135 type = ISC_LOG_TONULL;
136
137 if (fileobj != NULL) {
138 const cfg_obj_t *pathobj = cfg_tuple_get(fileobj, "file");
139 const cfg_obj_t *sizeobj = cfg_tuple_get(fileobj, "size");
140 const cfg_obj_t *versionsobj =
141 cfg_tuple_get(fileobj, "versions");
142 const cfg_obj_t *suffixobj =
143 cfg_tuple_get(fileobj, "suffix");
144 int32_t versions = ISC_LOG_ROLLNEVER;
145 isc_log_rollsuffix_t suffix = isc_log_rollsuffix_increment;
146 isc_offset_t size = 0;
147 uint64_t maxoffset;
148
149 /*
150 * isc_offset_t is a signed integer type, so the maximum
151 * value is all 1s except for the MSB.
152 */
153 switch (sizeof(isc_offset_t)) {
154 case 4:
155 maxoffset = 0x7fffffffULL;
156 break;
157 case 8:
158 maxoffset = 0x7fffffffffffffffULL;
159 break;
160 default:
161 INSIST(0);
162 ISC_UNREACHABLE();
163 }
164
165 type = ISC_LOG_TOFILE;
166
167 if (versionsobj != NULL && cfg_obj_isuint32(versionsobj))
168 versions = cfg_obj_asuint32(versionsobj);
169 else if (versionsobj != NULL && cfg_obj_isstring(versionsobj) &&
170 strcasecmp(cfg_obj_asstring(versionsobj), "unlimited") == 0)
171 versions = ISC_LOG_ROLLINFINITE;
172 if (sizeobj != NULL &&
173 cfg_obj_isuint64(sizeobj) &&
174 cfg_obj_asuint64(sizeobj) < maxoffset)
175 size = (isc_offset_t)cfg_obj_asuint64(sizeobj);
176 if (suffixobj != NULL && cfg_obj_isstring(suffixobj) &&
177 strcasecmp(cfg_obj_asstring(suffixobj), "timestamp") == 0)
178 suffix = isc_log_rollsuffix_timestamp;
179
180 dest.file.stream = NULL;
181 dest.file.name = cfg_obj_asstring(pathobj);
182 dest.file.versions = versions;
183 dest.file.suffix = suffix;
184 dest.file.maximum_size = size;
185 } else if (syslogobj != NULL) {
186 int facility = LOG_DAEMON;
187
188 type = ISC_LOG_TOSYSLOG;
189
190 if (cfg_obj_isstring(syslogobj)) {
191 const char *facilitystr = cfg_obj_asstring(syslogobj);
192 (void)isc_syslog_facilityfromstring(facilitystr,
193 &facility);
194 }
195 dest.facility = facility;
196 } else if (stderrobj != NULL) {
197 type = ISC_LOG_TOFILEDESC;
198 dest.file.stream = stderr;
199 dest.file.name = NULL;
200 dest.file.versions = ISC_LOG_ROLLNEVER;
201 dest.file.suffix = isc_log_rollsuffix_increment;
202 dest.file.maximum_size = 0;
203 }
204
205 /*
206 * Munge flags.
207 */
208 {
209 const cfg_obj_t *printcat = NULL;
210 const cfg_obj_t *printsev = NULL;
211 const cfg_obj_t *printtime = NULL;
212 const cfg_obj_t *buffered = NULL;
213
214 (void)cfg_map_get(channel, "print-category", &printcat);
215 (void)cfg_map_get(channel, "print-severity", &printsev);
216 (void)cfg_map_get(channel, "print-time", &printtime);
217 (void)cfg_map_get(channel, "buffered", &buffered);
218
219 if (printcat != NULL && cfg_obj_asboolean(printcat))
220 flags |= ISC_LOG_PRINTCATEGORY;
221 if (printsev != NULL && cfg_obj_asboolean(printsev))
222 flags |= ISC_LOG_PRINTLEVEL;
223 if (buffered != NULL && cfg_obj_asboolean(buffered))
224 flags |= ISC_LOG_BUFFERED;
225 if (printtime != NULL && cfg_obj_isboolean(printtime)) {
226 if (cfg_obj_asboolean(printtime))
227 flags |= ISC_LOG_PRINTTIME;
228 } else if (printtime != NULL) { /* local/iso8601/iso8601-utc */
229 const char *s = cfg_obj_asstring(printtime);
230 flags |= ISC_LOG_PRINTTIME;
231 if (strcasecmp(s, "iso8601") == 0)
232 flags |= ISC_LOG_ISO8601;
233 else if (strcasecmp(s, "iso8601-utc") == 0)
234 flags |= ISC_LOG_ISO8601 | ISC_LOG_UTC;
235 }
236 }
237
238 level = ISC_LOG_INFO;
239 if (cfg_map_get(channel, "severity", &severity) == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
240 if (cfg_obj_isstring(severity)) {
241 const char *str = cfg_obj_asstring(severity);
242 if (strcasecmp(str, "critical") == 0)
243 level = ISC_LOG_CRITICAL;
244 else if (strcasecmp(str, "error") == 0)
245 level = ISC_LOG_ERROR;
246 else if (strcasecmp(str, "warning") == 0)
247 level = ISC_LOG_WARNING;
248 else if (strcasecmp(str, "notice") == 0)
249 level = ISC_LOG_NOTICE;
250 else if (strcasecmp(str, "info") == 0)
251 level = ISC_LOG_INFO;
252 else if (strcasecmp(str, "dynamic") == 0)
253 level = ISC_LOG_DYNAMIC;
254 } else
255 /* debug */
256 level = cfg_obj_asuint32(severity);
257 }
258
259 if (logconfig == NULL)
260 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
261 else
262 result = isc_log_createchannel(logconfig, channelname,
263 type, level, &dest, flags);
264
265 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && type == ISC_LOG_TOFILE) {
266 FILE *fp;
267
268 /*
269 * Test to make sure that file is a plain file.
270 * Fix defect #22771
271 */
272 result = isc_file_isplainfile(dest.file.name);
273 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS || result == ISC_R_FILENOTFOUND) {
274 /*
275 * Test that the file can be opened, since
276 * isc_log_open() can't effectively report
277 * failures when called in isc_log_doit().
278 */
279 result = isc_stdio_open(dest.file.name, "a", &fp);
280 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
281 if (logconfig != NULL && !named_g_nosyslog)
282 syslog(LOG_ERR,
283 "isc_stdio_open '%s' failed: "
284 "%s", dest.file.name,
285 isc_result_totext(result));
286 fprintf(stderr,
287 "isc_stdio_open '%s' failed: %s\n",
288 dest.file.name,
289 isc_result_totext(result));
290 } else
291 (void)isc_stdio_close(fp);
292 goto done;
293 }
294 if (logconfig != NULL && !named_g_nosyslog)
295 syslog(LOG_ERR, "isc_file_isplainfile '%s' failed: %s",
296 dest.file.name, isc_result_totext(result));
297 fprintf(stderr, "isc_file_isplainfile '%s' failed: %s\n",
298 dest.file.name, isc_result_totext(result));
299 }
300
301 done:
302 return (result);
303}
304
305isc_result_t
306named_logconfig(isc_logconfig_t *logconfig, const cfg_obj_t *logstmt) {
307 isc_result_t result;
308 const cfg_obj_t *channels = NULL;
309 const cfg_obj_t *categories = NULL;
310 const cfg_listelt_t *element;
311 bool default_set = false;
312 bool unmatched_set = false;
313 const cfg_obj_t *catname;
314
315 if (logconfig != NULL)
316 CHECK(named_log_setdefaultchannels(logconfig));
317
318 (void)cfg_map_get(logstmt, "channel", &channels);
319 for (element = cfg_list_first(channels);
320 element != NULL;
321 element = cfg_list_next(element))
322 {
323 const cfg_obj_t *channel = cfg_listelt_value(element);
324 CHECK(channel_fromconf(channel, logconfig));
325 }
326
327 (void)cfg_map_get(logstmt, "category", &categories);
328 for (element = cfg_list_first(categories);
329 element != NULL;
330 element = cfg_list_next(element))
331 {
332 const cfg_obj_t *category = cfg_listelt_value(element);
333 CHECK(category_fromconf(category, logconfig));
334 if (!default_set) {
335 catname = cfg_tuple_get(category, "name");
336 if (strcmp(cfg_obj_asstring(catname), "default") == 0)
337 default_set = true;
338 }
339 if (!unmatched_set) {
340 catname = cfg_tuple_get(category, "name");
341 if (strcmp(cfg_obj_asstring(catname), "unmatched") == 0)
342 unmatched_set = true;
343 }
344 }
345
346 if (logconfig != NULL && !default_set)
347 CHECK(named_log_setdefaultcategory(logconfig));
348
349 if (logconfig != NULL && !unmatched_set)
350 CHECK(named_log_setunmatchedcategory(logconfig));
351
352 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
353
354 cleanup:
355 return (result);
356}
